\u0026yaw=231.49402\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://www.dentalcareseattle.com/contact","source":"dentalcareseattle.com"}],"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"105633734453980993161","name":"Dental Care Seattle (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105633734453980993161"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Downtown Seattle","street":"600 Broadway #330","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98122","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"from_the_business","name":"From the business","options":[{"name":"Identifies as LGBTQ+ owned","enabled":true}]},{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Language assistance","enabled":false}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible seating","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Pediatric care","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Gender-neutral restroom","enabled":true},{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"crowd","name":"Crowd","options":[{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true},{"name":"Transgender safespace","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Checks","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"On-site parking","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid parking garage","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid street parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Mariel Duchow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrB25Xmvl3DivJHzlKhna-Ji4EJO5Oa9yO9gNDLCvEvNcFW2Lt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Higgins and Angel are fantastic. I was originally scheduled for a new patient dental cleaning, but Dr. Higgins identified a couple of fillings that needed to be redone. She went through the images in detail and explained everything thoroughly. She did not try to upsell anything unnecessary, which I really appreciated. She’s extremely patient, knowledgeable, and personable.\n\nAngel truly lives up to her name - she made sure I was comfortable throughout the visit. Highly recommend this office.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anna Muller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJUtOAcvki6cGj-brkGNBZZPrOL4T2XhDROgoC5xawqRzf5dq9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been going here for around 5 years, and I love it. The staff are so kind and talented, informative and gentle. The new remodel is gorgeous, and it’s a very peaceful environment. I’ve recommended this practice and Dr Radandt to many friends and I’ll continue to do so. Thank you for taking good care of me!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chloe Donlan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbX6h5K7mjzU3SJNHZtRWkCApzhOn4Ctcq6lW1_99niz5vLeUg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have lived in three states and saw multiple dental practices in each. Hands down, dental care seattle is the best practice I have ever been to. If I move again, I’ll legitimately fly to and from Seattle to keep this dentist. Dr. Radandt, his entire team, and everyone at reception (especially Jennifer) are the most knowledgeable, patient, and kind staff. From routine cleanings to fillings, whitening, and issues with my jaw—they are thorough and take the time to listen to patient thoughts and answer questions. Kudos team!!! For the first time in my life, I actually look forward to my dentist appointments.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jacob Pavlik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJCJZFeu-83Op1CW84434w7WYxXFdr3ncAlJK4801OwQpcwag=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been a Dental Care Seattle patient going on 4 years and only have the best experiences to share. Their music is fun, staff friendly \u0026 helpful, hygienists resourceful \u0026 knowledgeable (request Quinn!), and dentists kind \u0026 personable (Dr. Shana Reidy is the best!). The comfort of the newly remodeled lobby is amazing. I love the chairs and sometimes wish I had to wait longer...","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paul Giglio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXidbskpzrm3MiFeLqKSoycgvOzWaZwN_4KhrCp4WIeC6BAxqpYjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dental Care Seattle is truly one of the best practices out there. Dr. Nick Radandt is an exceptional dentist who combines deep technical expertise with genuine care, empathy, and an easygoing warmth that instantly puts you at ease. You can tell he loves what he does and takes real pride in helping patients feel comfortable, informed, and confident in their care. He never rushes an appointment and always takes the time to explain things clearly, with a calm confidence that builds trust from the start.\n\nWhat really stands out is the entire team. From the front desk to the hygienists, assistants, and billing staff, every single person is warm, professional, and truly cares about your experience. The receptionists make you feel welcome the moment you walk in and actually remember your name! The hygienists are incredibly thorough but gentle, and the dental assistants are attentive and reassuring. Even the billing team goes out of their way to make everything smooth and transparent, which is rare and so appreciated.\n\nI previously had the same dentist for over 25 years and was honestly nervous about switching, but now I wish I’d made the move ages ago. Every visit feels like you are in the best hands, both technically and personally - and I can honestly say that it is enjoyable (which I never thought I'd say about going to the dentist!)\n\nIf you are looking for a dental team that blends professionalism with genuine care, Dental Care Seattle and Dr. Radandt are outstanding.\n\n—-\n\nA special shoutout to Becca, the best dental assistant I’ve ever met. She’s courteous, knowledgeable, and wonderfully attentive, but above all, she’s just an amazing human being. She has a way of making you feel completely at home and is such a valuable part of the team. One of the main reasons I decided to start Invisalign was because of her expertise, reassurance, and the confidence she inspired. She treats you like family and makes every visit comfortable and stress-free from the very beginning.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"kareem hosny","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUCnOO7bJl2zIGaACoTMZWqLqH78XwvysFJ1zjWTuGIFshEWw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"They charged me couple of times for procedures I didn't have. When I try to explain it and dispute it, they get a little aggressive. I was in a crown procedure (root canal is already treated, so no sensation in the tooth), where the dentist found a small cavity, on one side of the tooth. She said it was tiny, removed it in a second without any numbing injection. Only to look at the bill where they up charged the codes to a comprehensive procedure filling on multiple sides. Which means they upcharge me and my insurance for numbing I did not receive and drilling/fillings/treatment I did not receive. They also pressured me into deep cleanings almost every visit. I keep disputing these charges from them, however, they simply add a charge fee of a $13.1 a month on my billing for a service that I don't believe I had. I feel it is more of a business, where they try to bring more revenue than what actually need to be done clinically.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elizabeth Stenson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVtyifkVaqWk_OieWTwx9I-Q0qM4Lq-qtzs_pdEhY8gChpVMO8C6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been going to Dental Care Seattle since approximately 2009, and have always had great experiences. Not only are the staff always friendly and engaging, but I've also continuously been given quality advice regarding dental needs and help with insurance.\nMost recently, I was seen by hygienist Frankie, who was amazing. He was gentle and did a great job cleaning, but he also took the time to chat and get to know me as a person rather than just a patient. I appreciated his inquiries about my health history and making sure he understood how some of my medical conditions may affect our session.\nAdditionally, Hannah at the front desk was so friendly and helpful! There was another woman sitting to Hannah's left (I didn't get her name), who was also super nice and welcoming. Thanks for being great - I plan to continue with Dental Care Seattle for a very long time!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steve Speer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU5ABCUjztC45zjICh1p0YaRkr-FHNYDhTt-X9kg2uUcuY1APY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Can’t say enough about the care I received here. I went in looking to improve the look of my smile and Dr. Redenz sat me down and explained all they could do for me. After the consult and seeing what my smile could look like after treatment I went ahead with their plan. In just 5 visits I now have a completely new bright smile that I am proud to show off. The care I received was top notch and any question or concern I had was quickly addressed. Courtney, Angel and Dr. Redenz made me feel right at home and made each visit something to look forward to. I couldn’t be happier with my smile and will be back for all my dental needs.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
