026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://www.seattledentalco.com/","source":"seattledentalco.com"}],"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"111477924465174792988","name":"Seattle Dental Co. (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111477924465174792988"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Queen Anne","street":"100 W Harrison St Suite #150","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98119","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Chris Byrne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpsnf7zeTzvy4_iBR-m0DSQfuIFGCR6JgpX433mwHEMTe09wsI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Rarely do I share my impressions of a doctor, their colleagues, and their facilities, but in this case I will make an exception. From the moment I walked into the practice, I was made to feel welcome and appreciated. The waiting area is clean and tastefully furnished and the atmosphere is congenial. My visit involved an initial assessment, x-rays and cleaning. Justin was proficient in gathering details regarding my overall health, and efficiently took the necessary x-rays. Dr. Amanda Guerrero performed the inspection of my teeth as well as the cleaning itself. Kudos to her for routinely checking if I were comfortable during the process, which can often be distressing for some. At no point did I feel pain or discomfort. I was very satisfied with the results of the exam and the cleaning. The assessment that followed was comprehensive. It was clear that we needed to give special attention to some of my teeth. Together we formed an action plan that was both practical and holistic. Nicole at the front desk was very helpful in disclosing the details following my visit. She went over the costs for each of the procedures that were recommended by Dr. Guerrero, as well as what my insurance company would likely authorize, and most importantly, if any out-of-pocket expenses would be due when services were rendered. I appreciated the summary, and the ease of scheduling my next visit. I left feeling good about having chosen this practice for all of my dental needs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kristin Stinavage","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWGC91qE_lPwFeK6FueTOMST_gWVPm7y95MbQEyX3oM7ja885JOA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my first time visiting this dental office, and I had a truly positive experience from start to finish. I especially appreciated their streamlined communication. They offer a mix of texting and email, which works wonderfully for me. Given the nature of my work, it’s often difficult to hop on the phone, so having flexible communication options made everything much easier.\n\nThe intake process was simple and efficient, and it was easy to complete all the necessary forms before my appointment. The staff was kind, professional, and timely.\n\nThe dentist took extra time with me and was incredibly informative. Even in my mid-30s—having lived in a few different places and seen quite a few dentists—I learned a great deal. We discussed plaque, the anatomy of my mouth, and various factors that impact my day-to-day life, including sleep. I deeply appreciated the emphasis on sleep and breathing, as oral health plays such an important role in overall wellness. I walked away with new insights and practical information that I’m already considering implementing.\n\nBeyond their expertise, they were personable and even funny—we shared some light banter during a deep cleaning, which certainly made the experience more comfortable.\n\nI also appreciated how financially thoughtful they were. They were mindful of insurance considerations and worked to structure my cleaning in a way that helped minimize the need for additional appointments or unexpected costs. That level of awareness and transparency speaks volumes.\n\nThe office is conveniently located in downtown Seattle, and I most certainly plan to return. I’m grateful for their time, care, and thoroughness.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tara Senne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJY2MqJOD95APL7jBtMGcPznF7vjPgya8LZKatG_DI-Kj7g4w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The reception staff was friendly, organized, and transparent about procedure costs, helping explain estimates and coordinate future visits. The hygienist was thorough and made me feel at ease during my cleaning and X-rays. The dentist was very knowledgeable and took time to review my X-rays and clearly explain my treatment options. Highly recommend","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sam Kennard","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWakyfayl_FglBgSuuBT87ZZAFH5UqoQMzcO8K8q6zpFRdN8VV=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the best dentist I’ve ever had, and it’s not close. The entire staff is genuinely friendly, knowledgeable, and has superb communication. They’re also highly efficient—if my appointment is at 2 pm, you better believe they’re calling my name in the waiting room no later than 2:01. The hygienists and dentists are all excellent—they do quality, transparent work and manage to be professional and warm at the same time. Can’t say enough good things.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Olivia Dong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUI5s56SlARWwAtYsCCC2bD3CUzsO2gGVmw3WrfxD6G4o90wj7k=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was blown away by the care from the first visit! Everyone is so friendly and knowledgeable and takes time to explain my dental health concerns and symptoms to me with great recommendations for treatment. I never feel like the appointment is rushed and my teeth have never been happier!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Laura Murawski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQj6NH239O4hZUSGoaNRdD9ztXU8LcLdCweFZyZQxqb6UM5qB_zg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Shout out to Olivia and Dr. G for being an excellent team! The clinic is beautiful, staff and kind and professional. Dr. G took the time to really educate me on my dental health and establish both short and long term goals.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cathy Shiko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKu8EECMJgKqWhCIku2xDQV4YE4YBom85xhUKhLa7q64LPhBXxe=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Even though my husband has been coming to this practice for a long time, i was hesitant to establish care because i have really bad dental anxiety. I came in for my initial exam in June. I took off, and came back again in November. I can't express enough how Dr. Song was accommodating. She was not only gentle and patient, but i felt seen and heard. I have nothing but good things to say. Justin is so amazing. Thankyou!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Spence","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3p1hHmcCOtcCE56XMvUJYBX0Bx5RdrLG-5p_1NekVgoxpY7M=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had an extremely uncomfortable and unprofessional experience at Seattle Dental Co in Lower Queen Anne.\n\nI’m 35 years old, and instead of a respectful exam, the dentist repeatedly grabbed my jaw hinge and commented—multiple times—on how “overdeveloped” it was. The remarks were unsolicited, unnecessary, and made me feel embarrassed and self-conscious. I’ve seen many dentists over the years, and not one has ever spoken to me this way or treated my anatomy like a defect.\n\nShe then told me I should have had a palatal expansion and referred me to an oral surgeon for a $300 consultation, essentially implying that I should consider jaw surgery and braces at my age. This was presented with zero sensitivity and felt wildly inappropriate and unrealistic.\n\nI came in for routine dental care—not to be insulted, shamed, or pressured into extreme surgical interventions. Bedside manner matters, and this experience completely missed the mark. I left feeling worse than when I arrived, which should never happen at a dentist’s office.\n\nI will not be returning and would not recommend this practice if you value respectful, patient-centered care.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
