},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=OgimALORcqxZygRAkGbe4w\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=135.96869\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"/url?q=https://seattlesounddental.com/\u0026opi=79508299\u0026sa=U\u0026ved=0ahUKEwjh15OCpcSUAxXDDjQIHc5sAHQQqRkIICgT\u0026usg=AOvVaw3QybzFLWGuZy3RaTFypgUL","source":"seattlesounddental.com"},"owner":{"id":"111703910555880372048","name":"Seattle Sound Dental - Downtown (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111703910555880372048"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Central Business District","street":"509 Olive Wy #1024","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98101","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"crowd","name":"Crowd","options":[{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Kafiya Arte","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQJcM7mlj6fzpq0_AsBFQc6kVkJKCsR8UVirxLG46t6gELCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Two of my siblings and two of my close friends receive their dental care through Dr. Tanner. They rave about him all the time, so I knew that when I finally worked up the courage to see the dentist, I was going to see him. I’ve had a long time fear of dental procedures, and genuinely thought my loved ones were exaggerating over how much they loved Dr. Tanner. But I was completely wrong! Dr. Tanner is hands down the best dentist I could have ever imagined, let alone have the privilege to have experienced. He was thorough, educational, and efficient. He took the time to assess all of my dental needs in one visit, never rushed, and answered each and every one of my questions to completion. Somehow my follow-up treatment visit was even better! The procedure was painless, and he once again provided excellent education regarding what to expect during the healing process. I recovered well and am now able to enjoy food again. It was genuinely an incredible experience and I will be back regularly!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"D W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLcAkgQWU6RAAY7f1eOKFzWwYGH-AxV9V0yv5lVGghCNFAlbw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently moved to Seattle and I was looking for a dentist that was in my plan and I do read ratings/reviews . so I went to Seattle sound downtown Seattle and I love it!!!!!\nSome of the reviews stated that the office staff was not polite. I think they’re amazing. They were nice I’m very helpful with explaining their process and everything Then I met the doctor and he is awesome personality. Nice demeanor just very caring he listens you know and he explained the process and what would need to be done for a crown and everything.\n\nI even told my son that this dentist is great so he’s gonna look him up too👍🏼😉","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelcie Pittaluga","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4X2_5vhcnnU-bZa6WMWvGnhrLB76nyKrDlOLQ01ZI3JUBe1Asmg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As someone with debilitating dental anxiety, I can't say enough good things about this practice and every single member of their team! I've received phenomenal care from Dr. Tanner, Jesse, and Crystal after delaying regular visits due to a cross-country move and fears surrounding finding a team patient enough to deal with my extreme anxiety, and they've quickly converted me into a patient for life. Crystal in particular deserves a special shoutout - she is an absolute angel and could not be more patient or thoughtful, doing everything possible to put me at ease. I'm incredibly grateful to have found this practice, and can't recommend them highly enough!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matthew Armani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJt6-M_01s9ljT6CK0FeJHsG8Nscmgqy7_W-6Ta6oZzU0t7EA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went in extremely anxious due to past negative dental experiences, but the care I received completely changed that. I felt nothing but compassion and zero judgment, despite being very insecure about my teeth. A tooth that had caused me daily pain for years was saved with a root canal and crown instead of being pulled, and the result looks completely natural. I’m finally pain-free, confident enough to smile again, and no longer dread the dentist. I’m incredibly grateful to the staff and Dr. Nick Tanner for their exceptional care and highly recommend them. Special shoutout to Crystal as well.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ciji Munday","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDkyQHDUHSguGkrZ4Y2yoMjWuRbHkf5q2dK7dtNBoLhPNiw6w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Tanner and his staff are the best! They make you feel comfortable as soon as you arrive, and are really friendly and organized. Dr. Tanner listens well and is really good at explaining options, and the work he's doing which I really appreciate.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"LightInTheDark","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKI9o8jakU4qX_06H_vxzZN52dDFExzk5-iLg7JkhvHegbUnQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Horrible experience! The secretary is rude and intimidating! I went there only because I was seeing another doctor in that same building. The doctor himself is nice! However, the whole experience with this office is not worth the money and the nightmare afterwards. You pay for everything they tell you to pay for before you leave their office just to learn years later...that apparently you somehow owe them something... but it's too late because they already sued you and now the initial insignificant amount that you didn't know you owe them has quadrupled because they sued you (legal fees for court hearing you didn't know you had, no opportunity to defend yourself in anyway) and you receive a letter with court decision to put lien on your already very small paycheck. Just be aware of them practicing dishonestly, and be aware that even after you paid for everything that they told you to pay for there will be more that they will want you to  pay. Just be aware of the possibility of this scenario. There are better dental offices out there thank God!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Courtney Bay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEMevc5mN8D3CkIhgT6bLmys6JWZYUNN7HKKrh8-k17Z5icxY9ew=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"EDIT IN RESPONSE TO THEIR REPLY:\nIt wont let me reply to their comment but choosing to literally GASLIGHT ME and my experience by claiming I have the wrong office is insane and another reason to not support this business. Instead of taking accountability, they choose to gaslight.\n\nI never said you sent me to collections - I said the first time you made me aware of late payment was a threat to go into collections if i dont pay. My apt was in March and this didnt get resolved until August.\n\nDO NOT BOOK HERE - if they make a mistake or treat you poorly they will then choose to gaslight and deny your entire experience instead of take constructive criticism to just do better. Disgusting behavior.\n\n--------\nORIGINAL REVIEW:\nDid not have a good experience here. The dental cleaning I got took a super long time and I wasn't being rinsed/suction at all until a whole half of my mouth was polished. I was pooling in my own saliva the entire time. It was just uncomfortable and felt unprofessional.\n\nInsurance was difficult to figure out - I provided the correct information and months after my cleaning kept receiving bills for being uninsured and notices that if I didnt pay I would go into collections. The conversations I had on the phone trying to figure this out I feel were a bit rude and I felt like I was being scammed for money. My insurance carrier had told me they never received anything from the dentist all those months and I had to get my employer/company broker involved to get to a resolution.\n\nI was also recommended to get 8 fillings - this didnt feel right especially since at that point my insurance issues were unresolved and they had advised to just do the fillings and handle insurance later. And there was just no way 8 was needed when I had no issues at previous dentist. I did not move forward and got a second opinion at another dentist in the area and they told me at best I needed 2 and they werent that urgent. The new dentist told me they had absolutely no idea where anyone could have gotten 8 even if they were being nitpicky.\n\nThe doctor himself was extremely kind - so I did appreciate that. But with the reco for unneeded fillings and just overall experience with the cleaning and office staff dealing with  insurance - I would not recommend going Here","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Larry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLnDrYFnW9doCk9CAG9Q8vTyD8WPE55772Nu62hRq8gU6I51A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I had a mixed experience here. The staff were unclear about the actual costs, and I left unsure what I might be billed later. A friend who recommended this office ended up receiving surprise bills many months after her visit, which makes me nervous that the same could happen to me. I wish their pricing and insurance communication were more transparent up front. I had X-rays done and everything I was told looked great...a week later I had severe pain in one of my teeth that supposedly looked good on the x-ray and now I need a root canal. I'll have it done some place else now.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
