7suxSBcl5Zh5GQOr2Ro02JcE_3nEFH_Hy_6H8Bho2tvKj-blIKtL7tmwb1HszQ=w224-h298-k-no-pi0-ya60-ro0-fo100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"116114297153278083329","name":"Udistrict Smiles (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116114297153278083329"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Ravenna","street":"4530 Union Bay Pl NE UNIT 207","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98105","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Pediatric care","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"chris kurihara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIQJbSG69B4JNwLL2AWnKdFV0T8rJni_BIM9SIXuw4J9J-Gyw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr Bahl and her team are the best for family dentistry. Located near University Village, our kids love to walk around after our appointments.\nWe have been to some kid centric dentists and saw that the decor and atmosphere as attractive and kid focused but the actual dental work/ cleanings were the same as adult dentists with no personality.\nIt comes down to the wonderful personalities of Dr. Bahl, the hygienists, and front desk.\nOverall the best dental office we’ve been to. Dr. Ritu is the best with kids. I would have never imagined that my daughter likes to go to the dentist. A+++ Thank you for doing what you do!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Elizabeth L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUC51R-XW5KFUNNOddzeLneA1MsPxB8ku34jydmi91NkyK4TKC4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had my routine cleaning with Dr. Bahl and her team today. Both Dr. Bahl and hygienist Marilyn were incredibly sweet and friendly, and they did a fantastic job making sure my oral health is well taken care of. Special kudos to Marilyn for being especially gentle with my sensitive spots. She’s amazing! Thank you, Dr. Bahl and team☺️🦷","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kk bobo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXucD3_zd87d9QxAzvh7M9LjK06moGhpk53LDxvwgiifbQ-Y-I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I would not recommend this clinic, especially for patients unfamiliar with their insurance or dental options. I treated 4 cavities here and they had no pain, and I was not informed that “not filling” was an option. I was scheduled for treatments, including three fillings in one visit.\n\nI then had to return TWICE for corrections: one filling had a gap and needed to be redone, another created bite issues. One cavity caused a crack and led to chronic pain. I decided to treat it somewhere else and was advised to get an expensive crown to fix it.\n\nI also felt unsupported with insurance. I was referred to a provider that quoted thousands of dollars and charged hundreds for the visit not covered by my plan. I later found another clinic where the necessary treatment was fully covered.\n\nWhile the staff and Dr. Bahl are friendly, my experience raised concerns about the clinic’s quality, knowledge, and integrity. I recommend researching carefully before proceeding with treatment here.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Colton Clifton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUurvBpYd0bhufDNVZv-3VnDSrYbc8ZinuH1XzYFAZX6Api3Up2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I required immediate wisdom teeth removal and they got me in within 5 days and had them removed. They were efficient, communicative, and extremely hospitable. Would absolutely reccomend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Yi Zeng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLEQOEjoJ-XLZ1N29-REAwsUW_5ttZCLBHeGiKa7MRZGlDfqQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I don’t normally leave comments.  From my experience, Ritu Bahl is extremely unprofessional and passive aggressive about communication.  It is very stressful and distressing to work with her.\n\nI decided to transfer to a different dentist and asked for refund. There is still inconsistency within their staffs about the exact amount they need to refund me despite we had tons of text messages about it.  Worst experience ever with a dentist.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ayala Thomas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIPQQyDEyCh6bywznaol-wZN_9IIh_jVrCiBD4FEdhNNkjh=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent service and attention to detail. when I made the initial appointment, the office staff was very knowledgeable, courteous, and accommodating. They followed up consistently to ensure I filled out the forms, collect my insurance and to help prepare me for my daughter’s appointment. Dr. Bahl performed a thorough examination, educated my daughter about the benefits of wearing her retainer and solutions for sleep apnea. She made the visit pleasant with her sense of humor and caring approach. I highly recommend this dentist!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marie Wh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJWdlRHMSVBu6S4KUTuFnXZFQXhEkUXgvXPm72ed4X5kcshvQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Ritu Bahl made me feel instantly comfortable. She was kind and gentle and I appreciated her transparency and prioritization of patient care. She's the first dentist I've encountered who didn't try to sell me on the most expensive options for my dental needs, but stated that a specific treatment wasn't worth the time and cost. I loved that she said, \"if you were my family, I would recommend this...\" Dental visits can be anxiety-producing, but I left feeling good and look forward to her becoming my regular dentist.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Phil Keane","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWu6frhR0BKVmKLGkxcPHgocbLzq6wVr2_c5yoY0JSooIkPlLTI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"9/1/23 I've been having a toothache building that's getting worse the last few days, so yesterday afternoon I finally called up my dentist. They were taking off for a 4 day weekend, but were able to see me in Friday @ 11:30 even though they were closed. Doc Ritu came in, on her vacation, and as usual took great care of me. Even after I admitted to her that the pain was gone when I woke up that morning, she was still cool.\nI love these folks, I almost, almost... enjoy going to my dentist.\n\n10/ 21- 3 month cleaning appointment at my favorite dentist and crew.  Teeth cleaned by Annette (?), an excellent dental tech, (don't know proper titles) who has great Katy Perry's eyes. Behind her glasses, w/ binoculars and mask and other safety gear, they jump right out. Very knowledgeable and nice.\nI can't say it was \"fun\", but if I have to go to the dentist...it's always an  enjoyable experience with this crew.\n\nWhere else can you  get excellent dental care while discussing the merits of “ Little Shop of Horrors”? Nice folks.\nMy second time here, it was recommended by my daughter and 10 yr old Granddaughter. High praise there.\nGreat dental care with a sense of humor...\n👍\n1/24 - Just got me some flippers today.\nI’ve always wanted teeth I can pull out and show my  grandkids.\nThey feel comfortable right from the get go too, which I didn’t expect.\nOnce again, really nice people there, even the woman (she has a more important title I can’t remember) standing on my chest yanking the impression( for the flippers) out of my head.\nIts like I almost enjoy going to the dentist office when I go there.\nAlmost.\n3/10- Back for a cleaning. Always a pleasure to visit with Doc Bahl and her posse, despite having my dental work done there. Too bad it's not a coffee shop or a pizza place, then I'd look forward to going there. Oh well, that's life I guess,ay?\n\n8/11/25 Another trip to see my dentist. Actually her very competent right hand gal Ivy. A pretty easy gig this time for me, don’t know about Ivy, but she never falters and really no pain involved. I dozed off a bit and dreamt that Ivy \u0026. I were spelunking in the Ape Caves by Mt St Helen’s.(I was just reading about that area before I went) I was wondering if the caves were named that from olden Sasquatch sightings…\nAnyway,  time flew by \u0026 before I knew it l was back outside in Seattle’s version of Death Valley!\nAll in all it was another great adventure with my dentists office, although I missed Ritu’s smiling face today.\nTIL next time, Kids, keep smilin!\nPeaceOut\nPhil K.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0U3AGbUUd7SZigbIWMH8MhAfzZZDbHhdj36VdiiuwRd1U6HW5IReMmW_jJFyEmEwttOX4CBv0fywIkaIw4IUKNNcW4xR0IeEaVyDuG3Oz3ANKsMaUgf1c1M2MYw8xGMLU6kItBlhZKoLzV=k-no"],"When":"2025-8-12"}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
