ons":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Paid street parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Timotee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJHTAQydcGiCNqciFvveZb1JhugMaZF5eBWWIjuTepxKKBjyA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a great experience at this office today. Brie at the front desk was super warm and welcoming from the moment I walked in, which immediately put me at ease.\n\nSarah, the dental assistant, was incredibly friendly—definitely a people person—and made the whole appointment feel comfortable and easy.\n\nDr. Dhillon was very knowledgeable and took the time to explain everything clearly. I never felt rushed, and I genuinely felt cared for and supported in figuring out the best next steps.\n\nHighly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"William Holland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLZnMbik2ICGLQtRy_3OCKHe7l0nS_Y_ZG6G3s202lYOWW3vw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A Truly Outstanding Dental Experience\n\nI just had an emergency tooth extraction today with Dr. Minnie and her amazing assistant, Sarah, and I’m beyond impressed. From start to finish, they were fast, efficient, and incredibly friendly.\n\nProfessional \u0026 Courteous: They conducted themselves with the utmost professionalism and genuine kindness. I felt respected and well cared for throughout the visit.\nSpeedy \u0026 Efficient:They got me in as soon as I arrived, understanding that I needed relief before the weekend. The process was smooth and swift, with clear communication about what to expect.\nSweet \u0026 Reassuring: Their warm, patient demeanor helped ease my anxiety and made what could have been a stressful experience very comfortable.\nReasonable Payment Plans:On top of the excellent care, their payment plans are very reasonable, which made the whole experience even better.\n\nIf you’re looking for a dental team that combines expertise with genuine care, these are the folks to go to!!!!!I can’t recommend them highly enough. Thank you for taking care of me today and for ensuring I wouldn’t suffer through the weekend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Evan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJRIBppsESStZNtd7TJgXHb7kOXCbgc09W9Q4hcSZ7k6ECOdA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This office takes advantage of its clients and they hope you won't notice.\n\nI asked for a payment plan for my $200 copay. The manager first tried to sign me up for a credit card that I did not want. Once he finished, I sat down and received an email, notifying me that I agreed to a TWENTY FIVE DOLLAR \"convenience fee\". This was never disclosed to me in advance. I was never provided documentation of this fee. When I brought this up to the manager, he was incredibly dismissive, and tried to shift blame by saying, \"I just process the applications\". This answer tells me that they do this with everyone, and have been stealing people's money for years without notifying them of this outrageous fee.\n\nTheir payment plan claims 0% interest, but with a $25 fee, you're essentially paying 8% interest up front if you have a $200 cleaning like I did.\n\nHe offered to refund it to me, and was not able to provide receipt of the refund. Considering he already ruined my trust, I do not trust this office to actually provide me with the refund.\n\nFinally, when I called to make a complaint and ask for them to change the way they are selling this payment plan, the same manager answered and was even more dismissive. He told me he didn't see an issue with anything I told him, and did not find a problem with hiding the fee to their customers. He told me, quote \"This wasn't even $100, or $200\". Apparently, this office finds hiding a $25 fee completely okay.\n\nI have cancelled my next appointment with this office and will never return here.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6B65wir5Vf5CF-8j6VNmhdk1Qcl5vlgCu3l2OIriS68-s7WO4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Positives: Office personnel and dental assistants are friendly and polite. Scheduling/appt tracking is easy.  The practice uses modern technology (RBCT, they can build crowns in office).\nNot so great:   I came to this office looking for help after experiencing pain from a root canal and an unpleasant cleaning experience from another dental office.\n\nThe dentist told me  it was “common to be in pain for up to 6 months after a root canal\" (but I'd had them before and never experienced complications like this), and when I mentioned that  my tooth texture  felt gritty after the awful cleaning I had received,  my concerns were summarily dismissed.\n\nFor some reason, I trusted that terrible advice and came back 6 months later ,  this time for an emergency appt, when I couldn't stand the throbbing pain from the root canal anymore.  Only then did the same dentist who saw me 6 months earlier tell me there had been a visible abscess on the original X-ray, which she never  mentioned to me at my first visit, nor had she suggested treatment (other than pushing a $4k implant)...\nAgain, the dentist suggested the most expensive and invasive option, an implant..as a resolution to all the problems.\nWhen I pressed her about finding other options besides a costly implant , (like an apicoectomy), only then did she admit that their staff endodontist didn't offer those services and that she would offer a referral if I wanted that option.\n\nThe dentist  tried to convince me that spending $ on a re-treatment would be wasted, yet she couldn't actually prove or see that the cause of pain was from a fractured tooth root from the root canal.\n\nI left feeling  rushed, dismissed and gaslit rather than helped. The dentist was pushing pricey, extreme solutions that weren't  appropriate w/o proper further analysis and did not offer treatments options that might have been more appropriate/affordable simply because their staff didn't offer them.\n\nIf you have ongoing pain or a complicated case, I strongly recommend going to an actual endodontist.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sabrina Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAQxZw5UEZOYuZ8yI9W40MlzrRbJB_gV6pZ8UmeJoCTOJo2A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The staff is super friendly but the clinic is overall incompetent. This place is fine for annual check-ups but I wouldn't come here for anything else. I waited 40+ minutes in the treatment room because the technician who was supposed to take images of my teeth for a night guard \"forgot and went on break\" and everyone else was too busy socializing to notice. Then I was told my night guard would be ready in 10-14 days. A month passed, so I gave them a call and their front desk told me that she would get in contact with their lab and get back to me. Never heard back. Another month passed so I reached out again. Same girl picked up and told me that she would get in contact with their lab and get back to me. Zero follow-up again. A third month passed and a guy picked up this time and told me the same thing, but I wasn't going to be put off again so I made sure he actually got back to me. Well, he said it would be done in 10-14 days.... the original estimated timeline... it's almost as if someone forgot to send my images to the lab...","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alexandria Deavers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUw5VBF8lA88UtrU74b_bQvVc9Hqc5KsSXRzDnihKIpwZ7fqzYg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I will never go anywhere else for dentistry as long as I can! I absolutely love the staff; everyone is welcoming and fun to be around. Special shout out to Dr.Mimi, Azle, Brie, and Sarah!!! They are always very kind, funny, knowledgeable and clearly passionate about their jobs. I recommend them and this office to everyone I know. Thank y'all so much for making going to the dentist a great experience. (:","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Annabel Riggins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJWIrRj65jSm8qthbnrWNI5DmZd67HVix9RqzkqkQjUvEuGqtI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a great experience on my first visit. I experience a lot of anxiety during dentist appointments and Dr. Kehui Wang and Jesse were very helpful in explaining what they were doing, letting me take time before moving on to the next thing, and helping me understand how to better care for my teeth. Jesse's bedside manner in particular was more than I could have expected and he really helped me get through a tough cleaning! I was especially appreciative of the chance to sit with someone separately to talk about what each procedure from my treatment plan would cost and being able to apply for split payments. Thank you to the whole team!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"J K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTh1N3BnkXNitEXyciRAkupkglP52kMysmgxxV59Pw-Gi6BJ7umQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I've been here a few times for routine cleaning. Each time, the service felt rushed and done in an unusual order (like starting the cleaning with the polish). On my last visit, I brought up a concern with the dentist but it was not acknowledged or addressed. Overall, I don't feel comfortable with the level of care provided for routine cleaning or annual exams at this establishment. The office personnel and hygienists are friendly though.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
