{"input_id":"9e6f9253-3394-43b2-9086-2f7498150040","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Aurora+Dental+Care/data=!4m7!3m6!1s0x549016ae8d7650c5:0xdf2b3d4327ec9811!8m2!3d47.7042594!4d-122.3552365!16s%2Fg%2F1tknk41w!19sChIJxVB2ja4WkFQREZjsJ0M9K98?authuser=0\u0026hl=en\u0026rclk=1","cid":"16081014253098407953","title":"Aurora Dental Care","categories":["Dentist","Dental implants periodontist","Dental implants provider","Periodontist"],"category":"Dentist","address":"10314 Greenwood Ave N, Seattle, WA 98133","open_hours":{"Friday":["Closed"],"Monday":["8 AM–5 PM"],"Saturday":["Closed"],"Sunday":["Closed"],"Thursday":["9 AM–6 PM"],"Tuesday":["8 AM–5 PM"],"Wednesday":["8 AM–5 PM"]},"popular_times":{},"web_site":"https://www.auroradentalseattle.com/","phone":"(206) 729-0273","plus_code":"PJ3V+PW Seattle, Washington","review_count":161,"review_rating":4.6,"reviews_per_rating":{"1":15,"2":3,"3":0,"4":3,"5":140},"latitude":47.7042594,"longtitude":-122.35523649999999,"status":"","description":"","reviews_link":"","thumbnail":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHwZ0ijzYz1-MRxel_4IsZ1EDHkeIz2jfuXpL2_sfPRgclg9-Qdi7F-ksTFmnydGvmdlYdKCP3Tg2DITLNZxwt-axMuY66EY-veJKVoyuH-MLTSILC_EtIaONuB3hTxiGEq9Ybm9_-15pQ=w408-h278-k-no","timezone":"America/Los_Angeles","price_range":"","data_id":"0x549016ae8d7650c5:0xdf2b3d4327ec9811","place_id":"ChIJxVB2ja4WkFQREZjsJ0M9K98","images":[{"title":"All","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHwZ0ijzYz1-MRxel_4IsZ1EDHkeIz2jfuXpL2_sfPRgclg9-Qdi7F-ksTFmnydGvmdlYdKCP3Tg2DITLNZxwt-axMuY66EY-veJKVoyuH-MLTSILC_EtIaONuB3hTxiGEq9Ybm9_-15pQ=w436-h298-k-no"},{"title":"By owner","image":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/gps-cs-s/APNQkAHV0r8qWb57w-werg6e6OVW5UMj0A_I9dj_eDGPsRNLhripBox4ogrroGz_oRNTrDdaY2p_f7G5NTWK2veCvwsTq2KcY66-kF_93a3wqVvh_imuCLpKOnVm0R_VD2Y1MLr2VXARHpubKdgU=w543-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=x4hHDbLe5bJvxGGZzLZlag\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=52.869743\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"/url?q=https://www.auroradentalseattle.com/services/\u0026opi=79508299\u0026sa=U\u0026ved=0ahUKEwjKt9OEpcSUAxUqHzQIHRiFD5EQqRkIHSgQ\u0026usg=AOvVaw2fe-19SBOua7ZnnyzUgKUG","source":"auroradentalseattle.com"},"owner":{"id":"105533433525911832992","name":"Aurora Dental Care (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105533433525911832992"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Greenwood","street":"10314 Greenwood Ave N","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98133","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Sam_ D_","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNgk4NzZfm6YaD6LpAARe3GZgtfgBiKk07DlLlpehN2Jg4ReC1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My daughter was scheduled to have her wisdom teeth removed at 10:00 AM. We arrived at 9:40 AM and were told by the front desk that the doctor was running late and that we could leave and return in about 45 minutes. We did so and returned approximately 45 minutes later. However, we were still not checked in, and my daughter did not enter the operating room until 12:05 PM.\n\nDuring this extended waiting period, the front desk staff repeatedly attempted to add an additional product or technology to the procedure at a cost of $600. The staff could not clearly explain what this product was or why it was necessary. I repeatedly declined this add-on. Eventually, Dr. Layla Arab came to speak with me and stated that if I did not agree to this technology, she would not perform the procedure. I explained that refusing an optional product should not be grounds to deny medical care.\n\nHer response was dismissive. She insisted the product had been on the market for many years, although it later became clear this was a newer technology. She then stated that the product was not needed for the upper wisdom teeth but was “required” for the lower ones. When I asked why the terminology shifted between “recommended” and “required,” she was unable to give a clear answer. This made it appear that the product was optional but being presented as mandatory.\n\nThroughout this interaction, conversations occurred in raised voices in front of my daughter, causing her significant distress. She was crying, anxious, and under extreme stress due to the pressure and manner in which these discussions were handled.\n\nUnder pressure, I ultimately agreed to pay $300, after being told that only the upper wisdom teeth would be removed. After the procedure, the only staff member who treated us with professionalism and care was the anesthesia provider, who was polite and respectful.\n\nWe did not receive any written post-operative instructions or follow-up documentation. The only guidance provided was verbal information from a front desk staff member, and prescriptions were sent to the pharmacy. Since the procedure, my daughter has continued to experience anxiety, fear of bleeding, nighttime distress, and ongoing stress as a result of how the situation was handled.\n\nThe product listed on the paperwork is described as:\n“Placement of intra-socket biological dressing to aid in hemostasis or clot stabilization.”\nEach unit is listed at $250, yet we were initially asked to pay $600, and ultimately charged $300. If only one unit—or a partial amount—was used, it is unclear why the charge was not $250, and why the pricing was inconsistent.\n\nOverall, this experience involved excessive delays, poor communication, pressure to purchase an unclear add-on, lack of transparency in billing, and significant emotional distress to my daughter. This is not the standard of care I expected.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1jpqXq64BXEnSvGLERgciAfPrQMs9zSjMK1laRPtuKnOMaTtMfenuFWzw2jeYVl6XiRosekGbFFKPHekenFJAOCTwoBalMSdzL8YlnRbLet1C0iKZFIK-Gw0CJQHjzs5FVeG9jyKbgTJSI=k-no"],"When":"2025-12-21"},{"Name":"Madeline Minor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtZqpxtneQP183iyRuIw4hJg3QDwLpFHYKrLpOxi3rVhyiOUAI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the place I trust the most with the care of my teeth. Place feels very home-y and the staff all work well with each other, its clear they've all been doing this for awhile- very well oiled machine. When I have questions, the dentist answers me very clearly and with plenty of information.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"COMFORT INN SUITES","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-F9qY1f3zIXpFGHDdv9O3kIqPH_KfQgBRFxrhDOJJvE3pTm6a=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been waiting to get any dental work done for about 4years, and I was happy to come to this office. My tooth was saved and the team did an amazing job making sure my bite felt just right. Thank you - Yadi","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paul Sudthisa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIk9kn2jxWgJZwkChhzzwie2b7BKCcrcY1-YlUPO_TRtUoqJQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I just had my braces removed, and I couldn’t be happier with the results! It was a long journey, but Dr. Smith and the entire team at Aurora Dental Care took such great care of me every step of the way. They were always professional, kind, and made me feel comfortable during every visit. I’m so glad I chose them for my orthodontic treatment. My smile looks amazing now—thank you so much, Dr. Smith and staff!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shizhen Qin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLb7edRZ3htiQxyM8t1xD3Wbx_ISmHI4lTrqK29j3k5W7c8vQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Aurora dental care is so amazing. Going to the dentist is nothing enjoyable, but Dr. Smith and her team can make life much easier. With their patient-centered approach, they take patients’ comfort and satisfaction as their top priorities. At each visit, Dr Smith paid attention to my case and after a careful examination, she utilized the latest dental technologies with great skill to achieve the best results. She will go the extra mile to ensure the work done perfectly. Problem solved! the results are always amazing. The whole team from the front desk to dental assistants are very friendly and Skilled. I have been a happy patient of Aurora Dental Care for more than ten years. Highly recommended.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ev Stern","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNrRul1tgMQy-X_75HfRVzzOqt_t4plofKhuRGF3kqWb5Yc2G1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr. Smith is the best Dentist I've ever had.\n\nShe's performed her heroic work saving my teeth when I cracked them or needed a crown.  And otherwise I'm coming for cleaning and really enjoy all of the assistants there.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ellie Rapp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3H4fe2NzIsb-T8ixYkjEIseWag730sgXRdrLcC_hY_K-z-g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very warm and inviting Dental office! It’s a bonus that it’s covered by Medicare. The dentist remembered things about my family from our last visit six months ago for routine cleaning. Always a joy to go there.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Patrick Cook","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKjPyZ14ZWrUz4L7uBtXgRDWKvTBfdyZmhGZUclvgT-4AMJFw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been coming to Aurora Dental Care since the beginning of this year. I am very happy that I found Dr. Tuanh Smith, she took care of an urgent dental matter for me, and she was just great -- genuinely focused, understanding and professional. The front desk and the whole group at Aurora Dental Care are very pleasant to work with. From routine cleaning to crowns and fillings with Oscar and Dr. Smith everything has been explained clearly and treated with great care. The office is modern, clean and nice. I highly recommend this dental practice to friends and family in the Edmonds, Shoreline and Seatle area.\n-Patrick Cook","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
