JQdkm8Fz9rzv5SiVPYFnVvI1NFNfvpizrPTTUFvo1jZrZFmgQcv4yJudDEt7GS_KZ5Y4Tz9sdinSeOdtug4RduMN1T6-2tNcV-IQcz_hLmKqTc=w224-h298-k-no-pi-0-ya45.000008-ro-0-fo100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://www.localmed.com/widgets/070fd317-cad5-467a-9d4d-1f7594e6a3f4/","source":"localmed.com"}],"menu":{"link":"/url?q=https://ballarddentalarts.com/dental-hygiene/\u0026opi=79508299\u0026sa=U\u0026ved=0ahUKEwiz-emEpcSUAxXNyOYEHTFSAosQqRkIICgT\u0026usg=AOvVaw0KG0EVqTNooFGbEqGh0FFH","source":"ballarddentalarts.com"},"owner":{"id":"118406184594627582850","name":"Ballard Dental Arts (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118406184594627582850"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Ballard","street":"5803 15th Ave NW","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98107","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true},{"name":"Language assistance","enabled":false}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Cosmetic dentistry","enabled":true},{"name":"Emergency services","enabled":true},{"name":"Pediatric care","enabled":true},{"name":"Sedation dentistry","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"crowd","name":"Crowd","options":[{"name":"LGBTQ+ friendly","enabled":true},{"name":"Transgender safespace","enabled":true}]},{"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"On-site parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Pamela Sink","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDW22uMOzEKpRSQn83VwF8hFZ8CMFonpOk_qx-Jt4KktT8F3c=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! Can I just say that I LOVE MY DENTIST? After a very comprehensive initial appointment, I am actually looking forward to getting my mouth fixed. Nice to be at a practice that actually understands that patients want to be told the truth without judgments. Yes, I will take better care of my gums and teeth, now that you've explained everything clearly and not given me the usual moralizing lecture. Thank you!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bebe Labree","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXxR5niwOGTRU80oi6rmEqGrL89QWK4GtCnlaN4OUsQh8ozoY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everyone here is kind and friendly. I love that the equipment and technology here is also ahead of other dentist offices - it feels like I’m getting the best here, compared to other experiences I’ve had. I also love that I can make early appointments so that I’m done before I start work and don’t have to use any PTO to complete appointments. This is the most happy I’ve been with any Dental Office.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rick Jenkins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIg0cnknLkNJT42X1lv3YEaNmPlU624kVWHIFPujirkVX9UCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"To Ballard Dental Arts,\nI wanted to take a moment to share my most sincere thoughts regarding my Dental appointment last Thursday. I’ve been going through some things with, old number #19 for a few weeks now, and this appointment was to extract it. When I arrived at your practice, I was very stressed as I am sure you can understand. So, when I met Kristen, I was very nervous but with her calm, and confident vibe I started to relax a bit. Then when I met Dr. Dina I relaxed even more as she too exhibited the same calm, cool, confident vibe. As soon as I sat down in the chair I could hear some cool music playing in the background. Then once the procedure started Kristen started singing here, and there, and then when Dr. Dina joined in with the singing, and vibing with the music, I found myself trying to figure out how to laugh, and smile while my tooth was about to be extracted. Then when old 19 was about to come out both Kristen and Dr. Dina were singing, and grooving to the music as if nothing to see here. It’s just Thursday. So as I got a glimpse of #19 departing my mouth, I was literally body laughing to what I was experiencing.  With absolutely no stress, or body tension whatsoever. I told them both after that I felt like I was having lunch with them. I Only felt slight pain once due to the infection, and Dr. Dina quickly gave me more anesthetic. This without a doubt was my best Dental experience I have ever had, and as a result I never want to go anywhere else ever again. As I know I am in great hands when I visit Ballard Dental Arts.\n\nThank you,\nRick","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Charlie Newman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXweSmyszfAU68veNv62Ph0hWY3yLR4DG6fOrGB9V83Ougisz8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was waiting until I finished my run of appointments before reviewing-- but five stars for Ballard Dental Arts. Dr. Tobler and the five assistants/hygienists I've had have all been capable, effective, and compassionate. I hadn't seen a dentist in a long while, and was expecting some light shaming, but got no such thing. Feeling much better about my teeth, both now and for the future. Thanks team!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Prabha Dublish","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI2DxqRW3UE9-5FjgbeIgtp6gfI6GArjJlcQSA-lA3DHQLdzw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I’m extremely disappointed with my experience at this office. I called ahead to confirm my appointment, showed up on time, and was told it “wasn’t in their system.” On top of that, I was informed that my hygienist was suddenly unavailable — something they claimed they tried to notify me about, yet they never emailed or properly contacted me, even though they have my email on file.\n\nThis ended up wasting my time, my commute, and money I set aside for this appointment. The lack of organization and communication is unacceptable for a healthcare provider. I left without the care I scheduled and confirmed, and I won’t be returning.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Devlin Randolph","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJqyPBai-iBbZOeVlLwUPGAh5DG4gWpfwVnx-mVe0IJkFSEHA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Today was my first experience at Ballard Dental Arts, and it was great(if one can say that about going to the dentist). I usually have a bit of “ White Coat Syndrome,” but today I was very comfortable thanks to their amazing team! Tinker was thorough and engaging, Dr. Wang friendly and knowledgeable, while Travis was very informative and went above and beyond helping navigate my insurance concerns/options. I’m very happy to have found a dental practice that feels more like a community and less like a big box organization that treats you like a number. I’m looking forward to returning Ballard Dental Arts to help ensure my dental health, and knowing I’m genuinely cared about.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kayla Rust","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJIXFXUOKh1a0s0O8mvSseJzk1bP-1HJAJq31HSfAO0ORIrBg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everyone was very kind. And answered any questions I had. Nice environment! Would definitely recommend to other people!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rachel Seely","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4A1ib8UCRgWCBjek2hkvNzU13_Z09dur4VRn9uiBw-SomHrZSpg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My husband and I have been patients here for years, most recently with Dr. Tobler. After a lapse in our dental care, we tried to schedule a routine cleaning, but were told we would need to go through a full new-patient exam first, followed by a separate cleaning appointment. On top of that, they’re booking six months out. It feels unreasonable that something as simple as a cleaning is made so difficult to schedule. Unfortunately, I can no longer recommend this practice.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
