fYi5g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I went to this office a couple of times when they still accepted my insurance (Premera Blue Cross). At first, I really liked them. The staff were friendly, the view from the chairs was beautiful, and they even offered nitrous oxide, which I appreciated.\n\nUnfortunately, my experience changed after they stopped accepting my insurance. I had already booked a cleaning appointment, so I went ahead even though coverage was limited. During that visit, the hygienist suggested that I might as well stay with them because my insurance might not work well elsewhere—which felt more like a sales pitch than genuine advice.\n\nThey told me I had three cavities and implied that it was because I hadn’t chosen an optional fluoride treatment they recommended previously. I later went to another dentist (who does take my insurance) and brought the paperwork over. That dentist personally examined me and told me I had no cavities—just a few areas to watch. It really seemed like the original office was exaggerating or inventing problems to make money, which was disappointing and felt unethical.\n\nWhen I asked if they had recommendations for other dentists that took Premera, they told me to just look online, which wasn’t very warm or helpful either.\n\nOverall: if you have insurance they accept, you might have a decent experience. But based on what happened to me, I would be very cautious about trusting their treatment recommendations.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rachael","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUevc9f_malpG_X48VyOqD7DOnIlZCdJQVGjpzhHGsEuvkJ2ZfYNA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you have sensitive teeth and anxiety at the dentist, Seattle Smiles is the perfect place for all of your care. Not only is Dr. Nguyen a terrific and understanding dentist, but my hygienist, Lisa, is extremely gentle and caring. She warmed the cleaning water and took her time to make sure I was comfortable. The office is small and peaceful with an amazing view. I wish more people with dental anxiety could find this office for care.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Oz Harb","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViFj0-9DH4YEVZuLRgZaP1tbXGOxTKHiXN6JdmzqypQ9Duqmhzyg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful great people. The staff is all friendly and professional and the office has beautiful views.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jesse Grooms","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI7OQziX9-SaJyYpaHA_PoFVZ93jR3OpzMnpvFnSI1UXIzbCw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Seattle Smiles Dental, Dr. Nguyen, offers an exceptional experience. From the moment you walk in, her office staff and assistants are welcoming, professional, and attentive. I initially visited for Invisalign but was impressed by the thorough consultation, where Dr. Nguyen presented alternative options like porcelain crowns to address my gaps and spaces. Additionally, I expressed interest in Botox, and we had a thoughtful discussion about the process and expected results. I decided to proceed and am completely satisfied with the outcome. Dr. Nguyen is meticulous, taking the time to explain every detail and ensuring you feel prepared and comfortable throughout the entire process. I highly recommend her for both dental and cosmetic treatments!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nicole","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJDzhLVY-cxLQOYremkfrl68fpVtfbn5bv2qA04ORwFyVyvrQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everyone who works here is so kind! I have severe dental anxiety and none of the staff makes me feel embarrassed about it at all. They are helping me be more comfortable at the dentist every time, I would recommend them to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ali Tai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTRC1X0l-Agr1S7StRq6Mh-37EjAxuyerDeTLGYWxVOHdTta-w1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been a patient for nearly a decade, and this dentist office consistently impresses. The hygienists excel at leaving my mouth feeling refreshingly clean. Dr. Nguyen is attentive, gentle, and provides valuable recommendations. Plus, the predominantly female staff adds a welcoming touch to the overall experience. Highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"G/Johnny Gannardal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWx45211H4BLabqL0nssvBcoxX7taoJ4BVKA_j0FmPA60sRoU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"From start to finish I genuinely enjoyed my experience at Seattle Smiles. The staff is super friendly and always willing to go above and beyond to provide quality service to their patience. Scheduling appointments is easy, rescheduling is possible, and the warm greeting when you walk in the door is greatly appreciated!\n\nI personally enjoy the beautiful views of the city from the dental chair and the top notch service provided by Dr. Nguyen and her crew. I would TOTALLY suggest this office for anyone looking for a clean office that is customer friendly and on point with their service. :D","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ruth Haney","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-DHrnI-zIjg6igL1PXjNBoxRkNohKfQDMNlP1YlcXyYqzrlRw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been a patient at Seattle Smiles for over two years, and my experiences have been so consistently great that I felt compelled to acknowledge the team there in a review. Over the past two years, I’ve had regular cleanings, an emergency crown, a complete Invisalign treatment, whitening, and probably at least one other thing I’m forgetting - the team at Seattle Smiles is always a pleasure to interact with. Dr. Nguyen is professional and personable and put me at ease right away, as did her assistant Josie. They both are really great.  I appreciate how thorough Dr. Nguyen is at explaining what’s going on and what the options are.  I also feel like she and the team advocate for me with my terrible insurance company.  Alison is an amazing dental hygienist and makes me not dread having my teeth cleaned. I don’t know if it’s possible to actually enjoy a cleaning, but this is probably as close as you can get!  I also had a great experience with Dr. Asmeret, who saw me for a time sensitive appointment on a day that Dr. Nguyen was out.  Whomever I see, I feel like the experience is always seamless, which is a testament to how well the team works together. And finally, a special shout out to Brittany, who manages the front office. I really appreciate that I can book appointments and ask questions via email, and Brittany is super responsive and friendly with her correspondence. This office is good vibes all the way around. Oh, and the office itself – the design is neutral, professional, and welcoming. Beyond having a good experience at my appointments, I feel like my teeth and smile look their best under the care of this team.  Win/win!  Thank you, Seattle Smiles!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
