"id":"planning","name":"Planning","options":[{"name":"Appointment required","enabled":true},{"name":"Appointments recommended","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Payment plans","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"brenna mcbee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIJcZoP1nGZ7N0ak-kZGiCvJ-cQ3Xby4zSvuCvWySdQaamFbQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I HIGHLY recommend anyone to come here. I've always been so afraid of the dentist and had plenty of bad experiences, but coming here has completely changed the game for me. Dr. Rebekah and every single person who works here is SO kind and welcoming and genuinely just fun to be around. They really care about your experience and do a really great and thorough job making you feel comfortable and informed. I feel so lucky that I discovered Evergreen Smile Studio and never knew I could actually enjoy going to the dentist. It's really a one of a kind place!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIhuEEzhBlkEdkvAA5JQtifZFezbPpI-pQOKEYebEqapRtj5g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a fantastic experience at this dental office! Everything about the appointment was seamless, from scheduling the visit to every step of the experience in between. The space is super bright and spacious. I was really impressed by the scanner—such a cool piece of technology.\nDr. Nguyen was incredibly personable and knowledgeable, taking the time to explain everything clearly and making sure I was comfortable. I was super nervous but she put me at ease with her great sense of humor. So glad I found my new dentist!! Highly recommend Dr. Nguyen and team!!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn35wrhne02K5ajibStchJCRk3s37N0NLQKhlI99sPVOOVjP4SxJOL9rPpWn4zS3mmrCR_0I1YE36duLp5NzArA_OIp6DXdjBD14JE7Ki0SP3aXYiMKeFzlSW4SanAWKURx9DFDIUtlcV_af=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-25"},{"Name":"Maddi Alexander","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUv3WJ8PGx8zNFzEQ-XCH5IzzOwlbS8BMUuTV9W9RU1q5R1WA6q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this office! Going to the dentist can be intimidating for some, myself included, but the staff here are so incredibly friendly I don’t mind cleanings at all anymore. They are very knowledgeable, create a comforting environment, and I always enjoy our conversations. 12/10 recommend especially if you are not a fan of going to the dentist!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Vanessa Hester","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhMdT4PWKpe35c18w4zmY-pacJBQusWtxro2Nq5ELPV9vC6wc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been seeing Dr. Rebekah at Evergreen Smile Studio since she opened and I can't recommend her enough. She is very knowledgeable yet empathetic and provides recommendations that make sense for me. In addition to regular dental check up and a few fillings, she covered a discolored front tooth with a veneer that fit perfectly without any issues or side effects!\nIt's also great to see Dr. Rebekah's journey as a dentist. As I've been seeing her since she first opened the practice,  it's great to see her interest and investment in new innovative techniques and procedures and the overall growth of her practice!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"RK AHH Lions","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJvKWADIjyazhBERHyJYaMTOh3C7osR6UVnvbd2YA-SMr0SMA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great experience getting a crown on a molar. Office is new, clean \u0026 bright, and has very modern equipment. All the staff are super friendly \u0026 helpful. Dr. Rebekah Nguyen and her assistants took their time to create a crown that fits perfectly and is comfortable.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Susan Fedore","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfKB0FnpN5mlpgrjlTEtDQs5OVrdo0Zg70e09W5nuzBJ6kfzth=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Look no further for your new favorite dentist!  Three days after my long-time dentist retired, a filling popped out.  A friend recommended Dr. Rebekah and within five hours of calling, I was in the dentist chair.  The team at Evergreen Smile Studio made space for me at the end of their day where I was met with a warm, welcoming space, kindness, and incredible skill.  I have terrible dental anxiety and they completely put me at ease. My tooth was repaired and looks even better than it did before.  Big thanks and an enthusiastic 5-stars for this incredible crew!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"lucindayh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIp0jlwhKiaunXY4eQFCFsUi9WNDSNQRu3GiU7Ptl4KRxLrQA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"MAJOR INSURANCE ALERT to new patients. I booked my appointment 4 months in advance when their office told me they are in network for my insurance. Then 1 week before the actual appointment, they texted me they are out of network. Keep in mind. I filled out all the new patient forms 4 months ago. They decided to wait until last minute to tell me (maybe they wish they can still get my business out of desperation). If you are new to them, DO NOT TRUST what they told you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"F. “Kanga” S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1egtyyeE9N-NjSQkvYoTeojeRkYDbpB1BpLMtyNCUCBUfMLhN2A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I went to Eversmile Dentistry after an assault left one of my teeth damaged. I told Dr. Rebekah that I had victim-compensation coverage available for treatment. In my experience, she refused to consider it and required an out-of-pocket exam before discussing anything else. I paid the $79 because I needed help.\n\nBefore the appointment, she was responsive and attentive. Once the payment went through, that concern vanished. The shift was so sharp it was impossible to overlook.\n\nWhile waiting in the exam room, I stretched my leg behind the chair due to a knee injury. When she entered, the look she gave me felt openly judgmental, as if my posture had offended her. The exam itself felt unfocused. Her questions about which tooth hurt kept switching in a way that came across as careless rather than thorough.\n\nWhen I asked about treatment options, she said there was basically nothing she could do and that the tooth would eventually become very yellow. When I asked for alternatives or referrals, she gave a short laugh and said she didn’t know what to tell me since I didn’t have the money. Hearing that after spending my last $79 as a student was its own kind of clarity.\n\nHer demeanor throughout struck me as polished but emotionally vacant, the kind of surface presentation that gave off the same energy as Christian Bale’s character in American  psycho controlled exterior, no empathy underneath.\n\nThe patient coordinator, Devon, processed the payment immediately but never sent the exam results she said she would provide.\n\nAs I left, Dr. Rebekah brushed past me and gave me a look that matched the whole experience: dismissive and uninterested. I walked out feeling like a transaction rather than a patient dealing with trauma.\n\nSince then, I’ve found a different dentist  someone empathetic, professional, and actually committed to the standards the dental profession claims to uphold. My treatment is now fully covered, and I’m receiving real care from someone who treats patients like humans rather than inconveniences.\n\nThis review reflects my personal experience only, but based on that experience, I cannot recommend this clinic for anyone who expects empathy, professionalism, or meaningful guidance.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
