SSMNZm4OUhcREBv_6dehqF9blw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Let me tell you how my experiences goes. This place is amazing. The Doctors and the stuffs they are doing awesome job. They're friendly very well explained, very gentle through the whole process. I had always scare and  nervous when it come to visit dentist 😬. After my experience with them i wouldn't go anywhere else. Thank you SEATTLE ORAL CARE!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"P W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL--SWoHwb4EOvMMx19--nuQ5jhDWT_bt8Hrjxa3twVQBejDA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Their office staff are so lovely and kind. We had a bit of miscommunication with my insurance and I was left with an unexpected and large bill. I spoke to Tavi and she was very understanding and agreed to comp the bill due to miscommunication on their part. Over all my experience here was positive, and I would absolutely recommend them to others- just triple check they are actually in network with insurance!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pinyue Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKzxm_oNFxn1Fk3ee0mGOtTXgHYvk62GN0db7qKGvC8MLE12A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a fantastic experience at Seattle oral care. They are very professional, friendly, and made me feel comfortable throughout my visit. My cleaning was thorough, and my teeth feel amazing! They also did a great job with my retainer—everything fits perfectly. Highly recommend this office for excellent dental care!”","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ashley Batchelor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3CK-tbbqcYbxrHHssyMUX4RxwFVuNSn5FXtom6N01AKcljGDJ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Dr. Jere, the prosthodontist is pleasant enough to deal with. Dr. Amini, the surgeon is a highly unprofessional misogynist.\nMy elderly mother is in need of dental implants due to autoimmune issues. We worked with Dr. Jere to get her teeth extracted, temporary dentures, and a detailed plan for implants that we were ready to proceed with. After nine months and thousands of dollars of care, Dr. Amini showed up with a completely different diagnosis and plan from what Dr. Jere had prepared.  His bedside manner had the charm of a rotting bag of vegetables.  Naturally, we went in search of a second opinion.\nI have had a very difficult time getting Seattle Oral Care to send her records to the new clinic. When I finally was able to see the records myself, I expected a detailed diagnosis reflecting nine months of care and instead found only one sentence from Dr. Amini describing her condition and two long paragraphs of misogynist slander discussing her character. There were no details about her medical condition and how he arrived at his diagnosis. It is highly inappropriate to put things like this in a patient’s records and to share this with other surgeons she is consulting for a second opinion.  Defamation of women in their medical records is a well known, well documented issue in the industry and this is a shining example.  I will be submitting a formal complaint to the Washington Medical Commission.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mary Maresca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMlw4jOA4r81NaUgXg7DQBC1cwuPu_HkhnQ2UXPifjYxyeEVzE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dr Deepali’s  Dental Clinic was truly a blessing for me. I visited  other dental clinics before deciding for treatment here. It was a huge decision to remove all my bottom teeth for a denture\nThe results exceeded my expectations\nDr Deepali and her team provided comprehensive care from the thorough examination to the detailed treatment plan.\nDr Deepali and staff showed genuine care and compassion throughout the process. The personalized attention and emphasis on patient comfort make this practice exceptional. . Highly recommended for anyone seeking quality dental health care.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hannah Emmons","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKEPe_6POTyFSZLMeTICNBU6c4wz4l6gWrhWLv4Tv1MRneYwA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Started going here a year ago and it’s a very nice dentist office. Everyone is very sweet and helpful. I love the Dentist Assistant named Neha she is very gentle and kind!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tori Holic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIzJO0Z7DYXJbTp9CjQf2SxCyQI7B-ZM7jH8RiRtpHM4y_IBA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"IF THE CROWNS ON YOUR IMPLANTS FAIL\n…I HOPE THAT YOU'LL FIND THIS REVIEW FOR DR. DEEPALI JERE AT SEATTLE ORAL CARE\nI'm really grateful.\n\nIn 2010, a Seattle prosthodontist installed implants for two teeth in my upper jaw. My regular dentist attached the crowns. When the crowns for both teeth cracked in 2024, each dental practice had been closed for more than seven years. I had no record of my implants’ size, manufacturer, and platform. It was important to know my implants’ platform because some crowns screw in and others are cemented on.\n\nI spoke with a couple of oral surgeons who had no idea how to obtain this information.\n\nThe implants embedded in my jaw were still healthy, but only a fragment of each crown remained. I needed to find a prosthodontist who could:\n1) Remove the crown on each implant to learn how it mated with the implant.\n2) Use this information to identify the “make and model” of my implants.\n3) Order replacement parts.\n4) Make impressions of the implants, register my bite, and cast new crowns which fit together exactly with the teeth in my lower jaw when I bite down.\n5) Send me home with new crowns and a record of my implants’ size, manufacturer, and platform.\n\nThe original crowns were glued in, but Dr. Jere designed my new crowns so that they could be easily detached (unscrewed) if there is a problem to address in the future.\n\nMy implants are not commonly used in this part of the United States. I was very fortunate to find Dr. Jere. I would characterize the work she did as part “implant detective and part engineer”. She also worked with a veteran lab technician to create custom-made crowns which match my tooth color and tooth transparency.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kaylie Lemon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdnbEEwlbk6v6pNMPOEkujoJL5_JBqbaGP4EvQsc3-MQzdPdAY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is by far the best dentist office I’ve ever been to. The staff here are incredibly skilled and friendly. I always arrive feeling so welcomed and leave feeling taken care of. I’ve had my best dental checkups since visiting Seattle Oral Care and I truly believe it’s because of how personally invested I feel in taking care of my oral health at home. The advice and education given to me during my appointments has fostered a genuine desire to take better care of my teeth and gums. I believe this is what sets this dentist office apart from all the other offices I’ve been to in my lifetime.\n\nI cannot recommend Seattle Oral Care enough if you’re looking for a new dentist office.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
