ayments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"On-site parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Kit Moreland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-2Ox-rctRIR055pUBPI2SR2cGFb-A4B0IrskGfljNdo1TaC8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Visit 1: Booked a check up and cleaning. Lots of waiting around, eventually seen for the check up, told everything was fine but they wanted to replace 3 old fillings. They then told me the hygienist wasn't free so I needed to make another appointment for that and the fillings.\n\nVisit 2: Appt started 10 mins late. Had numbing injections given and told they'd be back in 5 mins once it kicked in. I was left for 30 minutes. Dentist and assistant got set up, put tools in my mouth then immediately announced that they needed to go back to a patient in another room - very cold and brusque experience even as I was saying I was pretty anxious.\nLeft for another 5 mins. Dentist and a different assistant came back - aside: literally no one introduced themselves or told me what their role was besides the dentist. Nor did they tell me what they are doing which I find very helpful for feeling comfortable. Once they did the fillings I asked about the cleaning and they said they hadn't noticed that on the appt and I'd have to book another appt for that because it was now closing time and they wanted to go home.\n\n3 hours later, one of my fillings fell out.\n\nThis was all such routine dental care carried out in the worst way I have ever experienced. Stay away.\n\nEnded up going to Megan Jones at Mountain to Sound Dental and had the most wonderful experience to replace that filling and get a cleaning.\n\nI had to call to cancel my follow up appointments, and I still got appointment reminders and I am now getting marketing spam to reschedule \"missed appointments\". I had to also call twice to have them email my x-rays over to the new dentist.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alex","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLv3EdHgcM6p76S2yy6vptANgLn91ezhm6Tpy3pULODS1TQCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"To be honest, avoid this place if you don't want a headache. I have been a patient here for almost 5 years, and it is always the same story: they issue a bill or estimate that seems fine, then 8 months later the head office calls claiming the insurance didn't accept it and demands more money.\n\nOn top of that, the front desk is not good at all. They are very rude and unprofessional. It seems their lack of professionalism is exactly what causes these statement issues.\n\nI strongly recommend that if you must visit this place, check your coverage with your insurance yourself. It feels like they intentionally put the wrong information on the paperwork to see if you'll pay more. Also, keep your pre-treatment estimates for at least one year to protect yourself from these crazy billing practices.\nWhy should patients have to deal with such wrong and unprofessional behavior?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chris Forbes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGUqAcHW5uCGxGpBrlsNqbtiOpS8NFRgmQ818Nc3Z-JsYEdQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing !! I’m so happy with the treatment ,front desk , the staff where all so nice and caring.. I had been to another dentist in the past and they were unable to extract my tooth.. I can say with all confidence this oral surgeon is calm, knowledgeable, and believer or not. The whole procedure was painless. I was terrified after so many bad experiences at other places.. It definitely gave me confidence in professionalism again❤️🙏🏻 Thank you so much..","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emma Fontaine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIBYJJAnPiDDpe3Wt2C2QU_hL11_OoJ9UskW1-hxfFHYbMCEg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I avoid writing negative reviews but I am honestly just shocked at how incompetent and uncaring the office staff are here. I work in healthcare and this level of incompetence would never be allowed.\n\nI came in in early December because I had something concerning going on with my gums. They told me they would refer me to UW oral surgery. I gave them a few weeks because it was holiday season and I know schedules are different. I called UW end of December and they said they hadn’t gotten a referral and to call northgate. I called Northgate and they said that was weird but they’d resend it anyways. Called UW again and they said they hadn’t received it but also wanted to check they took my insurance (which the didn’t) so I found south lake union dental to be referred to.\n\nI called Britenow and asked them to send in a referral to SLU. They confirmed the email to send it to and said they would get it out in a day or 2. Called SLU in a few days and they said they hadn’t received it. Called Britenow again and asked them to resend. They confirmed the email and said they sent it 3 times but they’d sent again.\n\nCalled SLU and still no referral. I explained what had been happening and the rep recommended I just have Britenow email me the documents so I could forward them. I called BN again and asked them to send me the referral and chart notes and X-rays. I had to call 10 more times that week (only got through a few times) and spoke to people who said that they had already sent them but they’d send them again. Finally they come through after 2 weeks but it’s just the X-rays and nothing else.\n\nAt this point they clearly have my correct email because the X-rays have come through. I call at least 30 times over the next 2 weeks and get through a number of times, each person telling me that they’ll send the referral and chart notes to me.\n\nFinally this morning I speak to someone and they promise they’ll send them over.  After the call I get a text asking to confirm my email. I confirmed it and they say they’ll send the info over now. After an hour I follow up letting them know I still haven’t received it. Finally after 3 hours I need to run errands and just go in.\n\nWhen I get there it isn’t busy and both the women are on their phones. I don’t mind when staff are on their phones when it’s not busy, but I’m confused about why they can’t call me and follow up about the text I sent hours ago. Especially when I’ve explained that I’ve been trying to get this referral for weeks.\n\nWhen I ask the woman to print my referral and chart notes, she offers to send it over email lol. Then she says, “oh, it looks like it bounced back”. She confirms my email and says “wow that’s definitely not what we had”…. How? You sent me an email with my X-rays last month and I’ve gotten in contact with you a dozen times at this point to confirm it. Also if you have been trying to email the wrong email for weeks (hypothetically) how many times has it bounced back and you’ve done nothing about it?\n\nI got the printout and left, but I still can’t believe the lack of integrity at this office. If I were sending a referral at the office I work at and found that it bounced back, I wouldn’t just leave it, I would call the patient to help figure out what’s going on. It’s unclear if there is something going on with their email, firewall, etc, but after this happened over a dozen times they should have looked into it.\n\nThese interactions left me with a bad taste in my mouth and feeling honestly even worse about the world. Healthcare is really high barrier in the US and even as a person who understands the system/works within it (and went out of their way to problem solve when the referral wasn’t working) I still had to call over 40 times and ultimately come in in order to get a referral I really needed.\n\nI hate reviews that are this long but this felt necessary (and was cathartic to write).\n\nHopefully these staff gain a heart and a backbone and realize that they’re in helping roles at some point but in the meantime avoid this office.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Stephanie Maeda","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUR9Esgb1x5ynuTUqFLO5t_f3trBgw_GOMQ4yM4ibOWn4-hgkWe=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The dental hygienists, assistants, and techs severely lacked professionalism and any regard for patient care. Usually I love going to the dentist and look forward to getting my teeth cleaned but this was a terrible experience. While getting my X-rays I asked to wear lead to protect myself and the tech responded that a banana exposes me to more radiation than an X-ray. Though this fact is true I wanted to limit my exposure to radiation when possible. I value and understand the importance of dental X-rays and wanted to have the x-ray completed AND protect myself.\nThe next hygienist who removed the plaque from the teeth was extremely rough, the cleaning was painful, and my gums were bleeding.  She asked how I was doing half way through the cleaning and I told her she was hurting my gums and her response was “huh” and she proceeded to quicken her pace and scrape my my gums just as intensely. She sprayed water all the way down my face and onto my neck and attempted to blot it off. There was still a lot of water on my neck/face so I asked if I could please have a towel to wipe my face and she responded “what water?”.\nFinally the last hygienist who polished my teeth was also unnecessarily rough when using the vacuum to suction water from my mouth. While my mouth was closed she repeatedly shoved the vacuum forcefully into the rear of my cheeks where it was painful. Additionally her hair was not pinned up and dangling in my face during the polishing.\nThe dentist herself was fine but did not say more than much more than everything looks fine to me.\nDue to the unprofessional experience and lack of respect toward patient comfort I will not be returning to Bright Now Dental and would never recommend this clinic to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Linda Hainline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGskqmQ2TowG9iklDnTq2GgFyXCwPM2qxMNqwjBUXpQxBrGd5f=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Was told a tooth needed to be extracted because it was loose and had no bone support. It was a tooth all by itself with nothing surrounding it that needed to be protected. Was quoted a price for a surgical extraction instead of a simple extraction. After working in the dental field for 40 years I challenged the coding but they wouldn’t budge. Found other issues while there for my first appointment so I will not be back or will not be recommending them to others.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"M. Mottware","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVawUNLrPQHdgGjg_DF_HmB8-AHc0qQrWUKZpbh-Fy4bWGVchkG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"When I was around 11 years old I went through some extensive dental procedures.  For years after I dreaded going to the dentist.  My last visit to Bright Dental Northgate was actually the best experience I have had in decades.  Highly recommended.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paul","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK14_EgNYLwSj8XY8mACjmFO4_tCclxzYXOx7wU0oD6EWUnkA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"An experience not to look forward to. Something totally amiss. Booked cleaning but got to be told I could only have an Xray and cleaning to be scheduled for a later date. They promised to get a braces insurance approval confirmed in 2 weeks. After 3 weeks, they stated I wait for 6 weeks. It is now more than 8 weeks and calls go unanswered","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
