,"name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"NFC mobile payments","enabled":true}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true},{"name":"On-site parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"James Luceno","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPbh6lAt8gWitkGFA7U-9YVCoZELMTqN_RCVNPJPJ5tk8fiaQ9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a great first visit at Wedgwood Family Dentistry. The office was organized, calm, and professional from start to finish. The hygienist was thorough and gentle, clearly explained what she was doing, and respected my preference for hand scaling (no cavitron) without any issue.\n\nThey carefully measured my periodontal pockets, confirmed stability, and made a thoughtful, conservative recommendation to continue periodontal maintenance. No pressure, no upselling—just clear explanations and good clinical judgment. The cleaning wasn’t painful at all, and everything felt unhurried and well-run.\n\nAfter a frustrating experience at my previous dentist, this was a huge relief. I’m very glad I made the switch and feel confident continuing my care here.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ibrahim baha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIgWJ9JBtcHoL-i9dylHf-6RdimBc_hV3dLViUqqUPxz4wWpw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is my first time coming here and had an awesome experience. The staff was super professional and really thorough. They cleaned my teeth well and made sure everything was checked out properly. I left feeling really well taken care of and my teeth feel great!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Carly Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKhGj5EKD4T_HOHlY5keuQmUUMcj33D0buTH7gq-GN4k20qCg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been to several dentists around the Seattle area in the 13 years that I’ve lived here and Dr. A with Wedgewood family dental has been by far the best experience I’ve had! All of the staff is extremely attentive, they were able to get me in for an emergency crown, and the facilities are upgraded and clean! 10/10 would recommend to anyone needing a new dentist!\n\nPlus, top pot being right across the street is an early morning dental treat!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jasmin Lim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIsYegOQnB_Npr4WDxsq65kZ1HNJwiibhd3e_-mhgJwxf-xjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Update: they reached out to me the day after I posted my review and offered a follow up complimentary cleaning. I was initially hesitant, but the hygienist who took care of me this time felt a lot more experienced and meticulous and I was very satisfied. I appreciate them reaching out and proactively addressing the situation although I wasn’t expecting it :)\n\nOriginal review: I had my very first cleaning \u0026 comprehensive exam at Wedgwood Family Dentistry. I was excited to try the practice out as there were many good reviews, but I was overall disappointed by the lack of detail and care from the hygienist.\n\nUsually when I get a full mouth X-ray or any procedure where there are equipment in my mouth, the hygienists/assistants are very careful to give clear instructions (open) or move slowly, but I felt like the hygienist only said “close” and moved the equipment around not very gently. I felt the same way when they were checking my gums as well, more pain/pricking than I have experienced in past exams across 3 different practices.\n\nI was also not super satisfied with the cleaning. It felt shorter than other cleanings I’ve had, and based on feel and look I didn’t notice a huge difference in the before and after.\n\nThat being said, everyone I’ve interacted with from start to finish were kind and friendly. I don’t know that I would go back based on my experience, but it was overall alright.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tyler Busey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURGDAiBdoBA1nyUdLkVbngq0Ke3AM1GrEGGk2EmOLQYq17E57czA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Confession time: it had been WAY too long since I had been to see the dentist until about 6 weeks ago when I walked into this incredible place. They are super professional and amazingly kind, from the wonderful people at the front desk all the way through the entire team providing the care. I could not recommend Wedgewood enough… they really went above and beyond for me.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Carla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL6uxXREZnIRLTYoRcZ6wYfDnh2lBOJiYH0MfPMrqo1IKVChw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Disclaimer- I gave this feedback privately and did not receive a response, so now I'm sharing publicly in the hope that it will be taken into consideration.\nTLDR - I’ve been going to WFD regularly over the last four years, and the professionalism and effort from the hygienists has steadily gone down hill. I'm honestly surprised at how high the google reviews are, given my experiences. The hygienist I saw this time was sweet, and seemed well-intentioned, but needed more training/practice, which is the responsibility of the business to correct.\n\n- The hygienist was distracted the whole time. She kept looking at the lobby while she was cleaning my teeth. She should NEVER have a sharp tool scraping my teeth unless she is looking at what she is doing. I’ve never had a hygienist do this. It was harrowing.\n- She did not thoroughly clean my teeth, though she was quite aggressive and did not have a light touch. The cleaning/polishing was probably 15 min total. She seemed to be rushing.\n- She did not understand how to use the water sprayer. It kept deflecting off my teeth and all over my face and I had water running down the sides of my face at several points during the cleaning.\n- During the cleaning one of the other tools started spraying water, which I didn’t notice until my pants were soaked and water was pooling up on the chair. She apologized but seemed like she didn’t properly understand how these tools worked, and it made me feel like I was not in confident hands.\n\nOverall, I would strongly encourage WFD to regularly assess your hygienists’ performance as I’ve had several mediocre experiences, with this latest one being absolutely unacceptable. I’m honestly shocked that your google reviews are so good. People must not be having the same experience as me. For what it's worth - Dr. Reza has always been pleasant and professional. No complaints there.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Allie H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKft32QSnqjRUUs7onho6pQ2MzBTSSoWmi3Ztv0s8-iHypL2A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just had my first visit to wedgewood family dentistry and it was excellent. Probably my best dental experience to date!\nI saw Pon for my cleaning and dr.mitchell for the exam. Amazing service as it was thorough, gentle, and no time was wasted. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aurora Utter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_LlaMLbBAJIsxUCBcY-LWXB7g35Rvmr_Px1eODyK5N_eM9kA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had an amazing experience at Wedgwood Family Dentistry! My preteen son needed a tooth extraction and has a pretty extreme phobia of needles. I was worried he would need to have general anesthesia to get through it, however I decided to giver Dr. Mitchell a shot first. I'm so glad we did!! Dr. Mitchell was extremely patient and professional, giving my son breaks and talking through things as needed during the whole experience.\n\nI appreciate the attention to detail and care taken to make my son's experience as pleasant as possible! The level of individualized care we received today made all the difference in the world to my reluctant kiddo. Our family will be forever clients! Thank you!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
